"'''Let Us Prey: The Whiphid's Tale'''" is a short story from ''[[Tales from Jabba's Palace]]'', which was published by [[Bantam Spectra]] [[December]] [[1995]]. The story tells the tale of the [[Whiphid/Legends|Whiphid]] [[J'Quille/Legends|J'Quille]]. It was co-written by [[Marina Fitch]] and [[Mark Budz]].

==Plot summary==
A [[Whiphid/Legends|Whiphid]] suitor to [[Lady/Legends|Lady]] [[Valarian/Legends|Valarian]], [[J'Quille/Legends|J'Quille]] - an [[Assassin/Legends|assassin]] and [[Spy/Legends|spy]] within [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] - is secretly on her payroll conspiring with [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba's]] kitchen [[Gender/Legends|boy]], [[Phlegmin]], to slowly [[Poison/Legends|poison]] the [[Gangster/Legends|gangster]]. However, J'Quille begins to be blackmailed, for someone knows about his plan and J'Quille has already been forced to pay 10,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] to keep them silent. With Lady Valarian's remote assistance, J'Quille discovers it was Phlegmin himself. But when the boy is [[Death/Legends|killed]] by a [[Dannik Jerriko|mysterious murderer]] who is loose in the palace. J'Quille's poisoning gambit evaporates, and he contemplates a more explosive way of eliminating the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]].

